g.text: Each client has a facade name aka uniqueId aka jsfIdentifier
There is a LeaseRefresher that periodically sends a BatonLeaseRenewRequest
to all clients, any interaction with the BatonManager extends the lease.
On first client registration, if firstClientTakesBaton is true then it will
assume the baton if it is not the server or an automated client.
JythonServer registers a client with the BatonManager via forwarding of addFacade()
The authorisationLevel is determined by asking the Authoriser
Creates the UDC Client by calling getUnattendedClientFacade() during configuration.
Creates the UDC Runner according to the gda.mx.udc.hyperion.enable property.
DeviceInterceptor is an interceptor on specific methods of Device, if the current thread
has an authorisationLevel below the protectionLevel of the device, and
the call is made from Jython the method call throws AccessDeniedException.
int addFacade(jsfIdentifier, hostname, username, fullName, visitId)
isServer and isAutomatedUser are determined by the authorisationLevel
Access is enforced in the client via calls to amIBatonHolder()
ApplicationWorkbenchAdvisor receives the BatonLeaseRenewRequest and uses IBatonStateProvider
to renew the lease by calling amIBatonHolder()
